{
  "ID": "GoR_MinnesotaTribe_SimpleBattle_TheBreakingPoint",
  "contractName": "The Breaking Point",
  "contractDisplayStyle": "BaseCampaignNormal",
  "difficulty": 12,
  "difficultyUIModifier": 0,
  "weight": 1,
  "scope": "STANDARD",
  "finalDifficulty": 0,
  "representativeCastDefIDOverride": "castDef_MarcusHammerick",
  "shortDescription": "[[DM.Factions[faction_RemembranceCell],Remembrance Cell]] perimeter forces have established defensive positions around the Armageddon facility on [[DM.StarSystems[starsystemdef_Fröislandis],<i>Fröislandis VII</i>]]. These are Joanna McEvedy's most fanatical warriors, deployed to protect what they believe is their people's only guarantee of survival. They know the terrain, they know what they're defending, and they will fight to the death.\n\nPrimary objective is complete elimination of all perimeter defenders. No enemy forces can be allowed to remain operational. Once these defenses fall, immediate assault on the inner facility will commence without pause for repairs or resupply.\n\nEnvironmental conditions are extreme. <i>Fröislandis VII</i> is a frozen planet covered in polar ice caps and tundra biomes. Temperatures are well below zero, visibility is limited by constant snowfall, and atmospheric interference degrades sensor performance. Heat dissipation will be excellent but mobility and targeting systems will be compromised.\n\nThis is a continuous operation. The moment perimeter defenses are breached, Phase Two assault on the production facility begins. There is no time to withdraw, regroup, or repair damaged units.\n\nFailure is not survivable. If perimeter defenders are not eliminated and the facility cannot be secured, Star Captain Marcus Hammerick will deploy the doomsday device. Complete destruction of all hostile forces is required.",
  "longDescription": "Boss, these are the fanatics protecting Joanna's final project. They know what we're here for and they'll die before they let us through. We kill them all or we all die. There's no middle ground.",
  "salvagePotential": 0,
